Child Abduction in China The problem of child abduction in China - reporter Steven Ribet speaks to a mother whose baby was snatched from her hands. In the southern city of Dongguan child snatchers have been finding easy pickings amid the chaos of the city's huge number of migrant workers. Transforming South Africa's wine industry Seven years ago he'd never even tasted wine, now Vernon Henn heads a thriving black-run wine label. Satire in Azerbaijan The bloggers in Azerbaijan facing five years in prison after staging a press conference with a donkey. Show less